definition: have plenty of/there's no lack of
to have/there is/there are/to exist/to be
of/~'s (possessive particle)/(used after an attribute)/(used to form a nominal expression)/(used at the end of a declarative sentence for emphasis)
variant of 是[shi4]/(used in given names)

sentences.english: Well, you're only younger once-there's plenty of time for that later.
sentences.chinese: 还是趁年轻尽情享受吧，以后有的是时间工作。

sentences.english: Some women experience that feeling with clothes, some with jewellery.
sentences.chinese: 有的女人在衣服上体会到这种感觉，有的是珠宝。

sentences.english: Alison: Uh, no, sweetie, we'll have plenty of time to talk later.
sentences.chinese: 哦，不，亲爱的，我们待会有的是时间说。

sentences.english: So basically what we have is this zinc plate here.
sentences.chinese: 我们主要有的是这个锌板。

sentences.english: History reaches out like an infinite line, which we only occupy a tiny fraction.
sentences.chinese: 历史伸向无穷象根线，其间我们占有的是很小的一点。

sentences.english: It is a holiday,so they have plenty of time for lunch.
sentences.chinese: 今天是假期，所以他们有的是时间吃东西。

sentences.english: And there, lurking among dozens of well-intentioned opinions, is a troll.
sentences.chinese: 潜伏在一些好的观点中有的是攻讦。

sentences.english: Make way, my friend, there's plenty of room inside.
sentences.chinese: 让一让，朋友，里面有的是地方。

sentences.english: The pies cut up well, there is enough for you.
sentences.chinese: 馅饼有的是，管你吃个饱。

sentences.english: He has much money with which he stunk.
sentences.chinese: 他有的是钱，他的钱多得都生锈了。

sentences.english: Of course, there is time for the Tories to fluff it.
sentences.chinese: 当然，托利党要犯错，也有的是时间。

sentences.english: Crammed full of film companies desperate for good idea.
sentences.chinese: 那有的是电影公司在望眼欲穿等着好本子。

sentences.english: They have trade competitors and rivals.
sentences.chinese: 它们有的是贸易竞争者和对手。

sentences.english: Some people owned two-storey houses with the ground floor used as shop and the second floor for living or storing.
sentences.chinese: 也有的是一楼一底，楼下为店，楼上住家或堆放货物。

sentences.english: I've got tons of room here, all reserved for Huaiyang food.
sentences.chinese: 我这里有的是地方，全都留给淮扬菜。

sentences.english: Transfer of not only the Olympic torch, the more love is long out of the torch.
sentences.chinese: 传递的不仅奥运火炬，更有的是长明的爱心火炬。
